1 olive oil
1 honey
1 water
1 soy sauce
2 Potato
1 Sesame Seeds
Garlic
1 Pear
1 Slaw Mix
1 Hoisin sauce
1 Plain Tofu
1 Ginger Paste
1 Asian Chilli Dressing
1 Crispy Shallots

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into fries.
• Place the fries and sesame seeds onto a lined oven tray. Season with salt and pepper and drizzle with olive oil. Toss to coat, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help toss the fries.

• Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice pear into sticks.

• In a small bowl, combine hoisin sauce (see ingredient list), the honey, water and the soy sauce. Set aside.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook pork loin steaks until cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate to rest for 5 minutes.
 ~~~~~~~~~~ MODULAR STEP ~~~~~~~~~~
• Cut plain tofu into 2cm chunks.
• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• When the oil is hot, cook tofu, turning occasionally, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a plate.

• Return the pan to medium heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook garlic and ginger paste until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the hoisin mixture and simmer until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes. Remove from heat, then stir through any pork resting juices.
• In a medium bowl, combine slaw mix, pear, Asian chilli dressing, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Toss to combine.
 ~~~~~~~~~~ MODULAR STEP ~~~~~~~~~~
• Return the pan to medium heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook garlic and ginger paste until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the hoisin mixture and simmer until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• In a medium bowl, combine slaw mix, pear, Asian chilli dressing, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Toss to combine.

• Slice the pork.
• Divide slaw, sesame fries and pork between plates.
• Spoon ginger and hoisin sauce over pork.
• Sprinkle over crispy shallots to serve.

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling over the crispy shallots!
 ~~~~~~~~~~ MODULAR STEP ~~~~~~~~~~
• Divide slaw, sesame fries and tofu between plates.
• Spoon ginger and hoisin sauce over tofu.
• Sprinkle over crispy shallots to serve.